commit.message: Break C++ exception translating code into a separate function.
Fixed C++ exception translation for overloaded binary operators.
Improved support for overloading unary operators.

Fixed returning types other than the expected pointer from operator&
overloads. Also fixed exception handling for operator&.

Fixed C++ exception handling for indexing when it is not used for
assignment.

Handle C++ exceptions when a call to an overloaded operator[] is
used as an lvalue.

Include utility code for exception handling in all cases where it is
needed.
Fixed exception handling for comparison operators.
Fixed cascaded comparison test failures.

Allocate non-reference temporaries for reference variables and
expressions.
Before, this would generate invalid C/C++ code where a reference was
declared but not initialized.

Fixed temporary handling for fake references while still allowing
temporaries for normal references to have their base type to prevent
errors involving uninitialized references.
Enable proper temporary and exception handling for logical negation.
Basic exception handling for assignment operations.
Added basic tests for exception handling for operators.
Test exception handling for cascaded assignment.

Properly distinguish between exceptions thrown by an overloaded operator[]
and an overloaded operator= when the exception handling routines are
different.

Added tests to make sure the correct exception handling routines are
called when different c++ exception handling needs to take place for
different parts of a given expression.

Make sure boolean coercions and function calls are allocated as
temporaries when they have an exception declaration.

Add an additional test that verifies that the exception handler for a
function call that is used as a right hand side expression for an
assignment to an index is properly separated from the exception handling
routines for indexing and assignment.

Changed tests for operator exception handling to be separate files rather
than a single srctree.

title: Fix exception handling for overloaded operators.
